      <source url="http://simonwillison.net/">Simon Willison's Weblog</source>
      <description>The popular Axios npm package was compromised after a leaked token allowed attackers to inject a malicious dependency, plain-crypto-js, into recent versions. The attack highlights the risks of supply chain vulnerabilities and the necessity of adopting trusted publishing to prevent unauthorized package releases.</description>
